2. DATA  (data/raw/*.csv and the derived data/processed/weathering.db)
================================================================================

The petroleum-products data is NOT covered by the MIT license above.

It is derived from the "Environment Canada Crude Oil and Petroleum Product
Database" (ESTS — Emergencies Science and Technology Section, Environment and
Climate Change Canada), published on the Open Government Portal:
https://open.canada.ca/data/en/dataset/53c38f91-35c8-49a6-a437-b311703db8c5

That source dataset is licensed under the Open Government Licence – Canada:
https://open.canada.ca/en/open-government-licence-canada

`data/raw/` contains the source table as released by ECCC. `data/processed/
weathering.db` is an adapted / derived version produced by the code in this
repository. In accordance with the Open Government Licence – Canada:

    Contains information licensed under the Open Government Licence – Canada.
    Source: Environment and Climate Change Canada (ECCC), Emergencies Science
    and Technology Section (ESTS) — Crude Oil and Petroleum Product Database.

This repository is not endorsed by or affiliated with ECCC or the Government
of Canada.
